25|$|The Vulgate {{continued}} {{to be regarded as}} the standard scholarly Bible throughout most of the 17th Century. Walton's London Polyglot of 1657 disregards the English Language entirely. Walton's reference text throughout is the Vulgate. The Vulgate Latin is also found as the standard text of scripture in Thomas <b>Hobbes</b> Leviathan of 1651, indeed <b>Hobbes</b> gives Vulgate chapter and verse numbers (e.g., Job 41:24, not Job 41:33) for his head text.|$|E
